'''Mizokui Shrine''' (みぞくいじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|lt=Ibaraki City|Q502403|qid=Q502403|1=Ibaraki, Osaka}}, {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|qid=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}}, and under the {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|qid=Q712534|lt=former shrine ranking|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} it was classified as a {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q134917326|lt=Fusha|1=Fu-sha}}. It is an independent shrine. Due to damage from the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=2018 Northern Osaka Earthquake|1=UNKNOWN}}, the protective buildings of the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=subsidiary shrines|1=UNKNOWN}} were rebuilt in a modern style. The former chief priest’s residence adjacent to the shrine was removed, and the shrine office was also rebuilt. On the 1st and 2nd of each month, amulets are distributed, and thanks to the efforts of the parishioners, the shrine’s rituals continue to be maintained.

